__DESCRIPTION__

Have you ever had 0.125 pizza? Maybe 1/8th of a pizza?
Theo van Hoesel who is a Math teacher explains the difference between the two.
Showing what 9/4/1/2 is, and what it is not.

Then he introduces [Number::Fraction](https://metacpan.org/pod/Number::Fraction)

[abstract](http://www.perlworkshop.nl/nlpw2014/talk/5308)



